              <p class="p2"><strong>Figs and dark chocolate</strong></p>
              <p class="p5">Got a nagging sweet tooth? Figs and dark chocolate are your ticket to indulging without too much guilt. “Figs are full of iron, antioxidants, fiber, and potassium," says Villacorta. "They're also known to be an anti-inflammatory food.” When it comes to chocolate, the darker the better. Aim for 70% cocoa or higher.</p>
